<br>
I'm a slow leveller (at 25+ days played) and don't ever expect or even want to be uber, lately i'v come back after perhaps my biggest eq-break ever (7+ months) to a 38th mage, which with thurgardin mines, DL's yeties and now Omen's bloodgills has stepped into 45th.<br>
<br>
For the first time ever i'v broken my old record gold amount (400pp) and have now pulled in almost 2kpp(most of it from the dwarf heads in thurgadin). My primary goal at the moment is more mana - More regen, more int, focus items or anything that can help my mana.<br>
<br>
Right now i'm aiming for a mount of some sort (pref. the new kind). but i'm intrested to hear some alternate ideas for what to aim at. Primarily it seems fairly impossibly for me to get focus 3 items (level 60 and lower) and focus 2 isn't gonna be much of value to me (being 44+), i was lucky to find the veil for cheap (think it was 100-200p). <br>
<br>
btw. is it just me or is there a huge hole, here? level 44-60 is a huge difference.<br>
<br>
Beyond that, i'm planning a extended delay at 51 or 52, because i never raided much and want to do the dragons, doing as many AA points as possible during that - possibly reconsider my guildless status.<br>
<br>
ps. i got ALL expansions and extensions.<br>
pps. i wear all the summoned focus items(5) and shard of the core. <p>~Aequi<br>
