<br>
As long as you haven't anything else to put into the slots, the summoned items are an ok solution. However, it is generally not worth keeping the shoulder and neck item equipped at all time. The shoulder item will make your self buffs last a bit longer and it isn't a bad idea to equip it while casting them, but after that I switch in something else. The same goes with the neck item, it is nice to save a reagent once in a while, but it really only have a great use at lv 60 using banishment.<br>
<br>
Your robe is ok for now and it is great that you have an enshrouded veil. For most of the other slots I would suggest loam stuff or nettet kelp. Nettet kelp has negative CHA but is otherwise great and you can just remove the items when you sell to a merchant.<br>
<br>
For your primary there are a lot of great items, but even a stein of moggok would be an improvement (something like 200pp usually)<br>
<br>
For neck item there a lot of great cheap items, and velium black saphire could be one of them.<br>
<br>
For the range slot is the beginners magic manual great. It is the result of two quests in PoK (you have PoK?) and only the second quest requires an item that costs something.<br>
<br>
Asside from that, use the bazaars search function and remember that a lot of ok items are better than one great.<br>
